  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of the study is to evaluate bone mineral density and muscle strength in
      survivors of bone marrow transplant. Association with age, type of transplant, steroids,
      years since transplant, body composition, endocrinopathies, radiation, quality of life and
      physical activity will be explored.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Bone marrow transplant survivors are at risk of diminished bone mineral density. Mechanisms
      and risks are not well understood. This study will help identify risks factors for
      developing this complication.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
